version: "v1.0-icns3-submission"
date-released: "2026-05-24"
license: GPL-2.0-only
repository-code: "https://github.com/digitalities/diffserv4ns"
url: "https://github.com/digitalities/diffserv4ns"
abstract: >-
  Stratum is a composable QoS substrate for ns-3 hosting Differentiated
  Services, Low Latency Low Loss Scalable-throughput (L4S), and Common
  Applications Kept Enhanced (CAKE) as three first-class clients.  Four
  pluggable primitives — Classify-and-Meter, Mark-and-Route, a per-class
  Slot array, and an across-slot Service Policy — let any client compose
  a queueing discipline by picking one strategy per stage.  The substrate
  inherits the 2001 DiffServ4NS ns-2 module as its classical-DiffServ
  client; the 2001 ns-2.29 sources are preserved verbatim under
  src/ns-2.29/ alongside a 2026 ns-2.35 port layer fixing nine latent
  defects without altering the 2001 design (companion archive
  10.5281/zenodo.19665019).  "Stratum" is a provisional codename for
  v1.0 pending peer-review and community feedback.
